Do you know anything about that?

1304
01:34:52,338 --> 01:34:53,305
No...

1305
01:34:55,274 --> 01:34:58,209
Well, mom told me, after...

1306
01:35:00,913 --> 01:35:02,175
After what?

1307
01:35:02,548 --> 01:35:04,914
After... she found out.

1308
01:35:08,687 --> 01:35:09,881
Look at me.

1309
01:35:13,092 --> 01:35:15,754
Are there things I should know and don't?

1310
01:35:16,762 --> 01:35:18,024
Oodles.

1311
01:35:19,465 --> 01:35:20,659
But if I tell you

1312
01:35:21,067 --> 01:35:23,126
you'll be annoyed
or you won't believe me.

1313
01:35:24,370 --> 01:35:26,770
I promise I'll believe you
and I won't be annoyed.

1314
01:35:28,908 --> 01:35:31,274
Mom's been appearing all the time.

1315
01:35:33,646 --> 01:35:34,840
To whom?

1316
01:35:35,114 --> 01:35:36,138
Sit down.

1317
01:35:42,421 --> 01:35:44,514
She was with Aunt Paula until she died.

1318
01:35:45,357 --> 01:35:47,348
It was she who called Agustina

1319
01:35:47,560 --> 01:35:50,120
and opened the door
so she could find the body.

1320
01:35:50,329 --> 01:35:54,060
It was she who put out the money
so they'd bring her bread

1321
01:35:54,900 --> 01:35:57,425
and who left everything paid
for the funeral.

1322
01:35:59,238 --> 01:36:01,035
Did Agustina tell you all that?

1323
01:36:03,142 --> 01:36:04,473
You don't believe me.

1324
01:36:06,779 --> 01:36:08,679
Agustina is crazy!

1325
01:36:10,049 --> 01:36:11,573
Last time we saw Auntie

1326
01:36:11,784 --> 01:36:14,582
you said yourself it was incredible

1327
01:36:14,787 --> 01:36:18,416
that she could live like that,
with her mind gone and half blind.

1328
01:36:18,791 --> 01:36:19,917
Remember?

1329
01:36:20,493 --> 01:36:22,654
Yes, I do, but what are you saying?

1330
01:36:23,596 --> 01:36:25,359
That she wasn't alone.

1331
01:36:26,732 --> 01:36:29,997
Who do you think made the wafers
and put them in tupperwares,

1332
01:36:30,202 --> 01:36:31,897
one for each of us?

1333
01:36:32,838 --> 01:36:35,671
Who do you think took the dolls
and Auntie's valuables

1334
01:36:35,808 --> 01:36:38,072
before the neighbors swiped everything?

1335
01:36:38,677 --> 01:36:40,042
Now do you understand?

1336
01:36:44,783 --> 01:36:45,977
Have you seen her?

1337
01:36:46,685 --> 01:36:47,617
Yes.

1338
01:36:52,625 --> 01:36:54,320
Is she, by any chance,

1339
01:36:54,793 --> 01:36:55,817
the Russian?

1340
01:36:57,029 --> 01:36:58,018
Yes.

1341
01:36:59,965 --> 01:37:01,262
Where is she?

1342
01:37:04,703 --> 01:37:05,897
In there.

1343
01:37:35,000 --> 01:37:36,092
Mom!

1344
01:37:37,203 --> 01:37:38,636
What are you doing down there?

1345
01:38:01,727 --> 01:38:03,285
Weren't you dead?

1346
01:38:04,630 --> 01:38:06,655
I've come back to ask you to forgive me.

1347
01:38:08,634 --> 01:38:10,431
I knew nothing about it.

1348
01:38:12,004 --> 01:38:13,665
I never even imagined it.

1349
01:38:18,377 --> 01:38:19,867
Come on, Paula!

1350
01:38:35,494 --> 01:38:39,055
My little girl!

1351
01:38:40,733 --> 01:38:42,200
The worst is over.

1352
01:38:43,168 --> 01:38:44,396
She's seen me

1353
01:38:45,070 --> 01:38:46,867
and she didn't reject me, did she?

1354
01:38:47,206 --> 01:38:48,230
No.

1355
01:38:50,276 --> 01:38:52,437
Did you really come back
to ask her to forgive you?

1356
01:38:53,746 --> 01:38:55,714
And also to be with you.

1357
01:38:57,616 --> 01:38:59,709
Some day you can explain it all to me.

1358
01:39:00,286 --> 01:39:04,450
Yes, and that day
I hope you understand me

1359
01:39:05,824 --> 01:39:07,689
and that you forgive me too.

1360
01:39:35,020 --> 01:39:36,578
I have to talk to her.

1361
01:39:37,690 --> 01:39:39,248
Why don't we go back?

1362
01:39:42,728 --> 01:39:43,820
Now?

1363
01:39:44,363 --> 01:39:45,421
Sure.

1364
01:40:12,758 --> 01:40:15,784
- I've dreamed about this so often.
- So have I.

1365
01:40:18,530 --> 01:40:19,895
I don't know where to begin.

1366
01:40:21,300 --> 01:40:24,758
You're not a ghost, are you?
You're not dead.

1367
01:40:25,270 --> 01:40:26,794
No, love, I'm not.

1368
01:40:27,973 --> 01:40:29,497
That's such a relief.

1369
01:40:30,476 --> 01:40:31,773
But even if I had died,

1370
01:40:32,611 --> 01:40:35,205
I'd have come back
to ask you to forgive me

1371
01:40:35,414 --> 01:40:36,904
for not seeing what was going on.

1372
01:40:38,083 --> 01:40:39,345
I was blind.

1373
01:40:40,586 --> 01:40:42,554
I found out the day of the fire.

1374
01:40:43,655 --> 01:40:45,247
Had you really left dad?

1375
01:40:46,258 --> 01:40:47,122
Yes.

1376
01:40:48,160 --> 01:40:49,684
I couldn't stand his cheating.

1377
01:40:51,463 --> 01:40:52,896
The afternoon of the fire

1378
01:40:53,565 --> 01:40:56,295
you rang and spoke to Auntie.

1379
01:40:57,269 --> 01:40:59,601
As usual, you didn't ask for me.

1380
01:41:00,172 --> 01:41:03,664
I got angry and told your aunt
you were heartless.

1381
01:41:04,576 --> 01:41:06,476
As I kept badmouthing you,

1382
01:41:07,646 --> 01:41:09,011
your aunt

1383
01:41:09,782 --> 01:41:11,409
defended you

1384
01:41:13,152 --> 01:41:14,744
and told me everything.

1385
01:41:20,692 --> 01:41:22,785
That your father had abused you,

1386
01:41:24,563 --> 01:41:26,292
that you'd got pregnant,

1387
01:41:27,466 --> 01:41:28,956
and that Paula

1388
01:41:29,535 --> 01:41:30,866
is your daughter

1389
01:41:31,470 --> 01:41:32,869
and your sister.

1390
01:41:34,973 --> 01:41:36,907
I couldn't believe it.

1391
01:41:37,976 --> 01:41:40,376
How could such a monstrous thing
happen in front of me

1392
01:41:40,579 --> 01:41:42,877
without me realizing it?

1393
01:41:45,517 --> 01:41:48,418
Then, I understood everything.

1394
01:41:49,655 --> 01:41:51,384
I understood your silence

1395
01:41:52,057 --> 01:41:53,786
and why you grew so distant.

1396
01:41:54,893 --> 01:41:58,590
I understood why your father
went to Venezuela.

1397
01:41:59,264 --> 01:42:01,892
He couldn't cope with the shame
of what he'd done.

1398
01:42:03,769 --> 01:42:05,134
I understood

1399
01:42:05,771 --> 01:42:07,864
why, after marrying Paco,

1400
01:42:08,440 --> 01:42:09,964
you went to Madrid

1401
01:42:10,809 --> 01:42:13,277
and wanted nothing to do with us.

1402
01:42:13,645 --> 01:42:16,478
I hated you for not noticing anything.

1403
01:42:17,149 --> 01:42:19,208
And you were right, love.

1404
01:42:20,619 --> 01:42:22,018
When I found out,

1405
01:42:22,554 --> 01:42:24,181
I was like a wild thing.

1406
01:42:26,058 --> 01:42:28,788
I went to the hut,
ready to scratch his eyes out!

1407
01:42:29,127 --> 01:42:32,119
I found him asleep
with Agustina's mother,

1408
01:42:32,397 --> 01:42:34,194
both of them worn out.

1409
01:42:34,566 --> 01:42:36,227
They didn't see me.

1410
01:42:37,002 --> 01:42:38,765
I set fire to the hut.

1411
01:42:39,771 --> 01:42:41,261
It was a windy day

1412
01:42:41,773 --> 01:42:44,970
and in no time the flames
had devoured everything.

1413
01:42:45,911 --> 01:42:47,811
They didn't have time to wake up.

1414
01:42:49,848 --> 01:42:51,941
The ashes in your grave

1415
01:42:52,518 --> 01:42:54,281
are those of Agustina's mother?

1416
01:42:55,587 --> 01:42:56,554
Yes.

1417
01:43:01,059 --> 01:43:02,117
Afterwards,

1418
01:43:03,395 --> 01:43:06,330
I wandered the countryside for a few days,

1419
01:43:07,399 --> 01:43:08,661
hiding,

1420
01:43:09,301 --> 01:43:10,700
like an animal.

1421
01:43:11,937 --> 01:43:13,734
I was going to give myself up

1422
01:43:14,439 --> 01:43:15,701
but first

1423
01:43:16,008 --> 01:43:18,602
I went to Paula's house to see her.

1424
01:43:19,978 --> 01:43:21,741
She was in a terrible state.

1425
01:43:23,015 --> 01:43:24,949
When she saw me

1426
01:43:25,217 --> 01:43:26,878
she wasn't at all surprised.

1427
01:43:28,086 --> 01:43:31,419
I came from the past,
where she was living.

1428
01:43:32,457 --> 01:43:36,188
She greeted me
as if I had just gone out the door.

1429
01:43:37,763 --> 01:43:41,062
With the tragedy,
she lost what little reason she had.

1430
01:43:42,067 --> 01:43:43,830
I couldn't leave her on her own,

1431
01:43:44,903 --> 01:43:48,100
so I stayed and looked after her

1432
01:43:49,308 --> 01:43:50,775
until she died.

1433
01:43:55,113 --> 01:43:57,673
In the village they think you're a ghost.

1434
01:43:58,317 --> 01:44:00,911
That's the good thing
about such superstitious places.

1435
01:44:01,386 --> 01:44:04,685
It was easier for me
to go along with them

1436
01:44:04,890 --> 01:44:06,289
than to speak the truth.

1437
01:44:07,259 --> 01:44:09,124
I thought I'd be arrested.

1438
01:44:09,795 --> 01:44:12,958
I never imagined
that no one would investigate

1439
01:44:13,265 --> 01:44:14,789
or punish me,

1440
01:44:15,634 --> 01:44:18,194
although all this time

1441
01:44:18,870 --> 01:44:21,395
I swear I've been in a living purgatory.

1442
01:44:26,878 --> 01:44:28,345
Never better said.

1443
01:44:49,067 --> 01:44:50,762
It's too early to go to the village.

1444
01:44:51,269 --> 01:44:52,668
We shouldn't arrive in daylight.

1445
01:44:52,971 --> 01:44:54,871
Why don't we drive by the river?

1446
01:44:55,641 --> 01:44:57,199
It's been so long since I saw it.

1447
01:44:57,709 --> 01:45:00,200
It's not what it was. It's dry.

1448
01:45:00,512 --> 01:45:01,809
How do you know?

1449
01:45:02,981 --> 01:45:05,916
Because there's a drought
all over Spain.

1450
01:45:06,118 --> 01:45:07,380
Don't you know?

1451
01:45:27,205 --> 01:45:30,800
We used to come here for picnics.
Remember, Raimunda?

1452
01:45:31,276 --> 01:45:32,140
Yes.

1453
01:45:33,311 --> 01:45:35,006
There was more water then.

1454
01:45:35,547 --> 01:45:37,071
I told you it was dry.

1455
01:45:37,816 --> 01:45:39,044
Shall we eat something?

1456
01:45:39,951 --> 01:45:40,747
Not for me.

1457
01:45:41,620 --> 01:45:44,145
- I'm going to eat a wafer.
- Me too.

1458
01:45:55,033 --> 01:45:57,228
This was your father's favorite place.

1459
01:45:58,470 --> 01:45:59,368
Paco's?

1460
01:46:00,372 --> 01:46:01,430
Yes.

1461
01:46:03,408 --> 01:46:05,273
It was the only thing he missed.

1462
01:46:06,044 --> 01:46:07,170
This river.

1463
01:46:27,799 --> 01:46:29,858
I'm glad he's resting here.

1464
01:47:00,298 --> 01:47:01,822
If Paula were alive

1465
01:47:02,634 --> 01:47:03,965
and could see us now,

1466
01:47:04,903 --> 01:47:06,336
all together...

1467
01:47:07,172 --> 01:47:08,605
She'd be so happy.

1468
01:47:15,914 --> 01:47:17,939
Have you always had such a big chest?

1469
01:47:19,151 --> 01:47:21,051
Yes, since I was little.

1470
01:47:21,419 --> 01:47:23,751
I remembered you having less.

1471
01:47:25,090 --> 01:47:26,580
Have you had anything done?

1472
01:47:26,925 --> 01:47:29,086
No! What a thing to say!

1473
01:47:29,694 --> 01:47:30,786
All right.

1474
01:47:31,062 --> 01:47:33,030
Grandma, did you ride the bike?

1475
01:47:33,265 --> 01:47:35,290
Yes, half an hour every day.

1476
01:47:35,634 --> 01:47:37,431
It's good for blood pressure
and the heart.

1477
01:47:37,636 --> 01:47:39,501
What did Aunt Paula say?

1478
01:47:40,572 --> 01:47:42,267
She roared laughing.

1479
01:47:45,944 --> 01:47:46,968
'Bye.

1480
01:47:50,348 --> 01:47:51,747
It's Aunt Paula...

1481
01:47:52,017 --> 01:47:53,211
Don't start.

1482
01:47:54,319 --> 01:47:55,445
I'll get it.

1483
01:47:56,688 --> 01:47:58,781
Hide mom's plate and cutlery.

1484
01:48:04,963 --> 01:48:07,193
- Who is it?
- Agustina.

1485
01:48:11,269 --> 01:48:13,032
We're having supper.

1486
01:48:13,505 --> 01:48:15,200
I'm sorry to bother you.

1487
01:48:16,308 --> 01:48:17,639
Don't stay out there.

1488
01:48:18,476 --> 01:48:19,465
Thank you.

1489
01:48:24,850 --> 01:48:27,410
Good evening.

1490
01:48:27,752 --> 01:48:29,777
- Sit down.
- Thank you.

1491
01:48:37,095 --> 01:48:39,928
I came to apologize about the show.

1492
01:48:40,699 --> 01:48:43,497
You shouldn't have done it.
It wasn't right.

1493
01:48:43,902 --> 01:48:45,062
I know that.

1494
01:48:45,303 --> 01:48:46,861
It's no excuse,

1495
01:48:47,339 --> 01:48:49,068
but they offered
to take me to Houston.

1496
01:48:49,307 --> 01:48:50,899
They cure everything there.

1497
01:48:51,743 --> 01:48:53,176
But I couldn't do it.

1498
01:48:53,812 --> 01:48:56,747
I'd rather die alone in my house,
but at peace,

1499
01:48:57,349 --> 01:48:59,044
and able to look you in the eye.

1500
01:49:01,720 --> 01:49:05,156
- Mom, I'm going to bed, all right?
- Yes, go on.

1501
01:49:07,325 --> 01:49:09,691
- Will you have some supper?
- No, thanks.

1502
01:49:10,061 --> 01:49:13,224
I heard you're going to sell the house.

1503
01:49:13,431 --> 01:49:16,229
We'd thought about it
but now we're here...

1504
01:49:17,035 --> 01:49:19,026
There are so many memories.

1505
01:49:20,572 --> 01:49:22,597
Well, I have to go.

1506
01:49:23,308 --> 01:49:25,435
Why don't you stay a while?

1507
01:49:25,944 --> 01:49:29,004
I have to go to the nurse
to get my injection.

1508
01:49:29,614 --> 01:49:32,344
In Madrid they told me
to learn to do it myself

1509
01:49:33,084 --> 01:49:34,381
but it gives me the creeps!

1510
01:49:35,253 --> 01:49:38,950
Your sister is unforgivable.
Leaving you alone like this.

1511
01:49:39,157 --> 01:49:40,454
Don't even mention her.

1512
01:49:41,593 --> 01:49:44,118
As I didn't say what they wanted
on television

1513
01:49:44,462 --> 01:49:45,861
she's not speaking to me.

1514
01:49:46,331 --> 01:49:49,732
She's very angry with me.
But I'm even angrier with her.

1515
01:49:50,402 --> 01:49:51,733
With good reason.

1516
01:49:52,037 --> 01:49:53,470
I envy you two.

1517
01:49:54,906 --> 01:49:56,339
You're so close.

1518
01:50:17,162 --> 01:50:18,390
Irene!

1519
01:50:20,398 --> 01:50:22,229
I've longed to see you.

1520
01:50:22,467 --> 01:50:23,593
Here I am.

1521
01:50:24,669 --> 01:50:26,227
I heard about your problem

1522
01:50:26,905 --> 01:50:29,373
and I can imagine how lonely you are.

1523
01:50:29,774 --> 01:50:30,866
Very lonely.

1524
01:50:35,046 --> 01:50:37,014
If only Paula were here...

1525
01:50:37,382 --> 01:50:39,543
I'm here to look after you.

1526
01:50:40,418 --> 01:50:41,908
You left the door open.

1527
01:50:42,520 --> 01:50:44,613
Don't worry, I closed it.

1528
01:50:45,390 --> 01:50:46,550
Did you go to the nurse?

1529
01:50:46,758 --> 01:50:49,056
No, I'm very tired. Tomorrow.

1530
01:50:49,794 --> 01:50:52,194
Tomorrow you'll be in a lot of pain.

1531
01:50:52,664 --> 01:50:55,132
Have you got the medicine
and the needles?

1532
01:50:55,333 --> 01:50:57,096
Yes, I bought it all in Madrid.

1533
01:50:57,302 --> 01:50:59,497
Good, I'll give you the injection.

1534
01:51:05,677 --> 01:51:07,406
I was born in this bed.

1535
01:51:09,147 --> 01:51:11,138
My mother slept here.

1536
01:51:12,417 --> 01:51:15,352
And in this bed
we held your sister Paula's wake.

1537
01:51:16,087 --> 01:51:17,349
I know,

1538
01:51:18,356 --> 01:51:19,983
and I'm so grateful.

1539
01:51:24,662 --> 01:51:26,960
We have to talk, Irene.

1540
01:51:27,732 --> 01:51:29,427
About everything you want.

1541
01:51:30,235 --> 01:51:32,328
But don't tell anyone I've come back.

1542
01:51:32,570 --> 01:51:34,800
Don't worry.

1543
01:51:36,908 --> 01:51:39,433
Thank you for not talking
about me on television.

1544
01:51:41,146 --> 01:51:43,273
It's our own business.

1545
01:51:44,349 --> 01:51:45,646
That's right,

1546
01:51:45,984 --> 01:51:47,815
and no one else's.

1547
01:52:56,054 --> 01:52:58,648
Mom, it's me, let me in!

1548
01:53:00,692 --> 01:53:02,523
What are you doing here? Come in!

1549
01:53:04,729 --> 01:53:06,128
I missed you.

1550
01:53:06,431 --> 01:53:09,958
- Are you going to stay here?
- Yes, until the end.

1551
01:53:10,468 --> 01:53:11,992
Agustina is very ill.

1552
01:53:12,637 --> 01:53:13,968
After what I did to her mother,

1553
01:53:14,172 --> 01:53:16,868
the least I can do
is look after her until she dies.

1554
01:53:18,476 --> 01:53:20,569
I have so much to tell you.

1555
01:53:20,778 --> 01:53:23,178
I haven't told you about Paco
or what I've done.

1556
01:53:23,381 --> 01:53:26,578
I'm dying to hear everything,
but go away now.

1557
01:53:27,051 --> 01:53:30,282
I'll see you every day.
Between us we'll manage.

1558
01:53:30,488 --> 01:53:31,580
Yes.

1559
01:53:34,492 --> 01:53:36,187
I need you, mom.

1560
01:53:38,997 --> 01:53:41,465
I don't know how I lived
all these years without you.

1561
01:53:42,567 --> 01:53:43,898
Don't say that.

1562
01:53:44,836 --> 01:53:46,133
I'll start to cry

1563
01:53:47,105 --> 01:53:49,437
and ghosts don't cry.

1564
02:00:55,700 --> 02:01:00,262
Translation: D. Mac Closkey


